The paper deals with image fusion, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of Latent Low Rank Representation (LatLRR) is a novel approach to image fusion, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the decomposition of images into low-rank and saliency parts, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of LatLRR also involves optimization techniques, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of weighted-average and sum strategies, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
